1
00:00:06,021 --> 00:00:08,720
“So ’ham” [saḥ aham], 
another māyāvādī’s expression.

2
00:00:09,276 --> 00:00:11,624
[A Drop of the Infinity is Infinite]

3
00:00:12,107 --> 00:00:15,476
That’s okay. What is ‘saḥ’?

4
00:00:16,434 --> 00:00:18,734
And he goes,
“Drop of the ocean and …”

5
00:00:18,734 --> 00:00:24,362
Okay. If the drop 
has certain qualities,

6
00:00:24,362 --> 00:00:28,295
then shouldn’t the ocean 
have those qualities also?

7
00:00:28,295 --> 00:00:32,564
As a drop of that ocean, 
we see you have so many qualities:

8
00:00:32,595 --> 00:00:36,675
you can see, hear, taste,
touch, smell and feel;

9
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:41,032
you can have
loving interaction.

10
00:00:41,172 --> 00:00:44,920
Cannot the ocean 
of which you are a drop?

11
00:00:46,427 --> 00:00:50,296
It has no such capacity? 
Impossible.

12
00:00:50,973 --> 00:00:53,833
Only greater magnitude.

13
00:00:56,299 --> 00:00:58,270
Infinitely loving,

14
00:00:58,270 --> 00:01:01,243
able to satisfy 
the hankering,

15
00:01:01,243 --> 00:01:08,252
the hankering 
of every atom of our soul,

16
00:01:08,329 --> 00:01:11,406
and not only of us—
of all souls,

17
00:01:11,406 --> 00:01:15,387
and not only that—
simultaneously.

18
00:01:16,139 --> 00:01:20,026
Akhila-rasāmṛta-mūrti 
is Kṛṣṇa.

19
00:01:22,425 --> 00:01:25,863
Like in 
Bhakti-rasāmṛta-sindhu—

20
00:01:25,863 --> 00:01:28,438
Mahāprabhu 
telling Rūpa Goswāmī,

21
00:01:28,961 --> 00:01:34,079
“The length and breadth 
of this ocean [of bhakti] is immeasurable,

22
00:01:34,570 --> 00:01:39,539
I can’t describe everything,
but I’ll take a drop

23
00:01:39,539 --> 00:01:44,051
and explain that.”

24
00:01:44,374 --> 00:01:49,078
And a drop of the Infinite 
is infinite,

25
00:01:49,772 --> 00:01:51,082
Śrīdhar Swāmī says it.

26
00:01:51,082 --> 00:01:53,543
So mukti, 
conventional mukti,

27
00:01:53,758 --> 00:01:58,079
is rejected in the pages
of the Bhāgavatam.

28
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:03,791
sva-rūpeṇa vyavasthitiḥ 
[SB: 2.10.6]

29
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:08,436
Jīva has this reality potential.

30
00:02:08,436 --> 00:02:12,191
As Guru Mahārāj said
quoting Einstein,

31
00:02:14,838 --> 00:02:18,674
“Reality is a thing 
plus something.”

32
00:02:18,674 --> 00:02:21,931
What? Its potential.

33
00:02:21,931 --> 00:02:26,081
It’s not just what it appears 
to be superficially;

34
00:02:26,081 --> 00:02:28,111
it’s in terms of its potential,

35
00:02:28,111 --> 00:02:32,240
its prospect—
the prospect of its capacity,

36
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:35,288
or the capacity
of it’s prospect;

37
00:02:37,149 --> 00:02:43,594
loving units 
reciprocating love and affection;

38
00:02:45,119 --> 00:02:47,565
Kṛṣṇa and Kārṣṇa;

39
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:54,259
as the ocean, so the drop.

